review_blob: Its a decent beer. You should probably save this one for when you go to Jamaica, its probably cheaper there. Not worth the money for what I paid for it in the US. No aroma, looks good, the taste is above average, overall its an average beer.

This beer is easy to drink...dont expect wonders, but its easy to drink, doesnt taste bad, is 5% alcohol and very light. Id drink this beer again, I guess it has gotten low scores because it is a lower quality beer, but its not a bad beer. We all need to drink the light stuff once in a while, I cant drink my expensive microbrews all the time.

The taste is a chocolaty caramel. Real easy beer to swallow and settles well in the stomach. I dont know where the "Milkshake" comes from because it taste nothing like a milkshake. The name is not important because this is a top notch stout.
I wish that I had spent my hard earned money on something else. I bought a variety pack and this was the best beer in the sample pack. I found this beer drinkable and others hard to stomach.
Good cheap piss beer to get smashed on. You get what you pay for. This is what you drink if you just want to get drunk on the cheap and you want to take several cacophonous shits the next morning.

The aroma is not anything special. The appearance is average. The taste is between I dont want to put this beer down and I dont want another one. I like the alcohol content and the beer is soothing on the stomach despite high alcohol content.
